<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2736">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2736', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2736&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 110</div><div>Votes Against : 14</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2736'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2736" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 110</div><div>Votes Against : 14</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2736'))">96</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2736', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2736&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2736"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2736-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2736">Scientists should not be required to obtain pre-approval from public affairs before responding to a media request&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3991-4049">21stCenturyRTK </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Agency policies should spell out a clearly defined role for the PAOs, including timely response to media inquiries and providing journalists and agency staff with accurate information, but should also prevent them from being gatekeepers of information. Scientists should not be required to obtain pre-approval from public affairs before responding to a media request. However, requiring scientists and researchers to give public affairs prior notice of such interactions when possible, and to recap the interview afterwards, is appropriate.<br/><br/>- From the 21st Century RTK Agenda</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2736" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2736', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=2736')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2736"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=scientific openness">scientific openness</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=media">media</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=science">science</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2736"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2732">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2732">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2732', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2732&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 41</div><div>Votes Against : 7</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2732'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2732" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 41</div><div>Votes Against : 7</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2732'))">34</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2732', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2732&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2732"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2732-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2732">Agency employees are responsible for the accuracy and integrity of their communications&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3991-4049">21stCenturyRTK </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Agency policies should make clear that employees are responsible for the accuracy and integrity of their communications and should not represent the agency on issues of politics or policy without prior approval from the Public Affairs Officer. Employees are also responsible for working with public affairs to make significant research developments accessible and comprehensible to the public.<br/><br/>- From the 21st Century RTK Agenda</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2732" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2732', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=2732')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2732"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=scientific openness">scientific openness</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=media">media</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=science">science</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2732"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2731">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2731">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2731', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2731&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 66</div><div>Votes Against : 5</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2731'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2731" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 66</div><div>Votes Against : 5</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2731'))">61</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2731', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2731&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2731"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2731-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2731">Scientific Review and Comment on Government Products&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3991-4049">21stCenturyRTK </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Scientists and researchers also have the right to review, approve and comment publicly on the final version of any document or publication that significantly relies on their research, identifies them as an author or contributor, or purports to represent their scientific opinion or relates to their field of expertise. While editing by non-scientists is at times necessary and useful, final review by scientific experts is essential to ensure that accuracy has been maintained in the clearance process. In order to accomplish this and create broader public input on scientific materials, agencies should be required to make available for public review and comment all research and documents cited and/or used in a final decision or action.<br/><br/>- From the 21st Century RTK Agenda</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2731" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2731', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=2731')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2731"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=scientific openness">scientific openness</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=media">media</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=science">science</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2731"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2728">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
<div id="DiscussionTopicVote_2728">
<div id="IdeaScale_Vote" align="center"><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2728', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2728&vote=1')"><img alt="Vote Up" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_up.gif"/>&nbsp;Looks Promising!</a></div><div style="padding:5px;font-size:2em"><a onmouseout="setTimeout('Bubble.hide()', 500)" onmouseover="Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 70</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2728'))" style="text-decoration:none;" id="TopicVote_2728" href="javascript:Bubble.showTip('<div>Idea Created : 10 days ago</div><div>Votes For : 70</div><div>Votes Against : 6</div>', document.getElementById('TopicVote_2728'))">64</a></div><div style="padding:3px"><a href="javascript:ajaxInlinePopup('DiscussionTopicVote_2728', '/akira/discussionVote.do?dbid=2294&topicID=2728&vote=-1')"><img alt="Vote Down" border="0" style="vertical-align:middle" src="/images/ideascale/vote_down.gif"/>&nbsp;I'm Not So Sure...</a></div></div>
</div>
</td>
<td valign="top" style="padding-right:30px; padding-left:20px;">
<div id="Idea_2728"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/2728-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2728">Scientific Freedom & Agency Media Policies&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/3991-4049">21stCenturyRTK </a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Agency media policies should respect that scientists and researchers have a right to express their personal views. Scientists and researchers, like any federal employees, have a right to express their personal views outside of a few narrow restrictions. Provided that scientists make an explicit disclaimer that they are speaking as private citizens and are not seeking to represent official agency policy, they should be allowed to speak freely about their research and to offer their scientific opinions  even in situations where their research may be controversial or have implications for agency policy. Agency policies governing communication with the media should make this option clear and explicit to employees. Such a personal views disclaimer does not, of course, cover the release of information that would otherwise be illegal, such as classified or personal information. Additionally, agencies should be encouraged to create a mechanism to allow non-scientific employees to express their opinions on actions, research, or policy within their areas of experience.<br/><br/>- From the 21st Century RTK Agenda</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_2728" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_2728', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=2728')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_2728"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=scientific openness">scientific openness</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=media">media</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=science">science</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_2728"></div>
</div></td>
</tr>
<tr id="row_2710">
<td width="120" align="center" valign="top" style="padding-left:10px;">
